          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pan is very hot, add the <strong>seasoned</strong> <strong>rump steak[s]</strong> and the<strong> halved cherry tomatoes</strong></p><p>For rare, cook for 2 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 2-3 min on each side; for medium, cook for 3-4 min on each side</p><p>Transfer the <strong>cooked rump steak[s]</strong> to a clean plate to rest, and keep the tomatoes in the pan</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>spaghetti</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>spaghetti </strong>for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked spaghetti</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> to the spaghetti and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the steak is resting, return the pan to a medium heat and add your<strong> tomato paste</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>sugar</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle of olive oil if your pan is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>halved olives</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>soy sauce</strong> and a splash of the <strong>reserved pasta water</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until thickened – this is your <strong>pizzaiola sauce</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>drained spaghetti</strong> to the pizzaiola sauce and cook for 1 min further or until warmed through – this is your <strong>spaghetti pizzaiola</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2015.-step-6-x400.jpg",
